# Hybrid tableaux (combination tableaux)
- The best or worst of both worlds, depending on who you ask.
    - The good: indicates both violations and constraint preferences
    - The bad: not as clear as either VTs or CTs (collectively harmonically bounded), columns and rows don't mean the same things in CTs and VTs (but in a HT they're treated as equivalent) 

